com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage

Enum AdobeAssetErrorCode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<AdobeAssetErrorCode>
      • com.adobe.creativesdk.foundation.storage.AdobeAssetErrorCode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<AdobeAssetErrorCode>

    public enum AdobeAssetErrorCode
extends java.lang.Enum<AdobeAssetErrorCode>
    AdobeAssetErrorCode defines the types of the storage failure.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • AdobeAssetErrorBadRequest

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorBadRequest
        The request cannot be completed. This typically means that there is something wrong with the url, the data or the file system. Repeating the request will most likely not help.

      • AdobeAssetErrorNetworkFailure

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorNetworkFailure
        This error indicates a (likely temporary) problem with the network. This could be caused by a server that is down or just too slow to respond.

      • AdobeAssetErrorUnexpectedResponse

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorUnexpectedResponse
        A response from the server did not match its anticipated form and therefore could not be processed. This could be caused by an unexpected HTTP response code or missing/malformed data. Typically this indicates a (temporary) problem with the server or the network.

      • AdobeAssetErrorOffline

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorOffline
        This error indicates that the device doesn't have a network connection.

      • AdobeAssetErrorCancelled

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorCancelled
        This error indicates that the operation was cancelled.

      • AdobeAssetErrorAuthenticationFailed

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorAuthenticationFailed
        The request failed due to an authentication failure, such as missing or incorrect credentials.

      • AdobeAssetErrorServiceDisconnected

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorServiceDisconnected
        The service is disconnected. This most likely happened because too many requests have failed.

      • AdobeAssetErrorConflictingChanges

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorConflictingChanges
        Both the local copy and the copy on the server have been modified. This error can happen when trying to push local changes to an asset on the server.

      • AdobeAssetErrorFileReadFailure

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorFileReadFailure
        Reading from a file has failed. This error can happen when a file fails to upload because it can't be found or read.

      • AdobeAssetErrorFileWriteFailure

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorFileWriteFailure
        Writing to a file has failed. This error can happen when a file fails to download because it can't be written to local storage.

      • AdobeAssetErrorExceededQuota

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorExceededQuota
        An upload has failed because it would have exceeded the quota on the account.

      • AdobeAssetMissingJSONData

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetMissingJSONData
        An attempt was made to use an empty JSON payload.

      • AdobeAssetErrorUnsupportedMedia

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorUnsupportedMedia
        The data returned by the server does not match the requested type. This error typically occurs when requesting a rendition of a file type that does not have one, e.g., a .json or .dmg file.

      • AdobeAssetErrorWrongEndpoint

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorWrongEndpoint
        An attempt was made to reference a server asset using a URL that is not compatible with the service on which the request was made.

      • AdobeAssetErrorNotEntitledToService

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorNotEntitledToService
        The requested action or component isn't allowed by the entitlements defined for the currently logged in user. This error typically occurs when attempting to access a service that is not enabled by the user's account administrator.

      • AdobeAssetErrorTimeout

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorTimeout
        Cannot reach cloud endpoint.

      • AdobeAssetErrorForbiddenRequest

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeAssetErrorForbiddenRequest
        Network forbidden error.

      • AdobeNoStorageSpaceInDeviceToDownload

        public static final AdobeAssetErrorCode AdobeNoStorageSpaceInDeviceToDownload
        If a large file is saved to device in loki and if there is no storage space to download. This Error is thrown.
